data.text:
Fengtai, Beijing, China

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 39.858425, 116.287148.

Lying southwest from Bejing city center, the district of Fengtai is one of the most modern parts of Beijing, which is functioning as a separated settlement. It was established during the times of the Western Han dynasty, and it has 14 sub-divisions, with 7 smaller townships. There are small industrial areas in Fengtai, as well as a few points of interest like Wanping Fortress, a few local parks and green zones. There are 790,000 people.
